<p class="style3">THE REPRODUCTIVE HEALTH ACT</p>
<p class="style1">Part 3<br />
Socioeconomics</p>

<p class="style1">By<br />
Senator Miriam Defensor Santiago</p>


<p style="text-align: justify">It is easy to discuss reproductive health in abstract terms such as theology, constitutional law, or international law.  But it is not so facile to exchange arguments over the hard facts concerning mother and child among the very poor.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify">Statistics on Maternal Health[1]</p>

<ul>
	<li>
	<p style="text-align: justify">Due to childbirth- and pregnancy-related complications:</p>
	</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify" class="style5">11 MOTHERS DIE EVERYDAY!</p>
<p style="text-align: justify" class="style5">3,000 to 5,000 mothers die every year</p>
<p style="text-align: justify" class="style5">162 mothers out of 100,000 live births die</p>
<p style="text-align: justify" class="style5">11% of all deaths among women of reproductive age in the Philippines are maternal deaths</p>
<ul>
	<li>
	<p style="text-align: justify">How many women will be affected by the RH bill?</p>
	</li>
